gerbv
------------------------------------------
Gerbv is an open source Gerber file (RS-274X only) viewer. Gerbv lets you load
several files on top of each other, do measurements on the displayed image,
etc. Besides viewing Gerbers, you may also view Excellon drill files as well as
pick-place file

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.7-1
  libcairo2-1.14.12-1
  libgdk_pixbuf2.0_0-2.36.11-1
  libgerbv-devel-2.7.0-1bl1
  libgerbv1-2.7.0-1bl1
  libglib2.0-devel-2.54.3-1
  libglib2.0_0-2.54.3-1
  libgtk2.0-devel-2.24.32-1
  libgtk2.0_0-2.24.32-1
  libintl8-0.19.8.1-2
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  bison-3.0.4-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-6
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://gerbv.sourceforge.io/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/gerbv/gerbv-2.7.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack gerbv-2.7.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./gerbv-2.7.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/gerbv-2.7.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/gerbv-2.7.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgerbv1-2.7.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgerbv-devel-2.7.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

